Now that Miss Mei is sick,

51
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:31,340
I'll leave you alone.

52
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:32,740
Get some rest.

53
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:36,340
Take care, Your Majesty.

54
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:43,100
This old woman

55
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:44,100
not only went to the Eastern Palace

56
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:45,540
but also came here to find me.

57
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:48,020
Are you okay?

58
00:02:51,220 --> 00:02:52,100
Shan.

59
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:53,860
Who is she?

60
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,420
Why did you bring her here?

61
00:02:55,780 --> 00:02:57,580
She is... She...

62
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:02,620
It's hard to explain.

63
00:03:02,740 --> 00:03:04,100
Simply speaking,

64
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,140
we must come to the palace together.

65
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:07,220
Otherwise, we'll both be in trouble.

66
00:03:08,740 --> 00:03:10,260
Be honest with me.

67
00:03:10,420 --> 00:03:11,660
Is she threatening you?

68
00:03:12,580 --> 00:03:13,420
No. No.

69
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:15,140
She can't threaten me.

70
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:16,580
It should be the other way around.

71
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:19,180
Why do you talk and behave

72
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:21,180
like a completely different person?

73
00:03:24,620 --> 00:03:26,020
Oh... By the way,

74
00:03:26,140 --> 00:03:27,620
what's in this box?

75
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,420
I almost forgot.

76
00:03:29,420 --> 00:03:29,900
What is it?

77
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:31,260
It's all your favorite food.

78
00:03:31,860 --> 00:03:32,460
Here.

79
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,580
What is this?

80
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:39,340
It is a Stewed Melon with Longjing Tea.

81
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:41,540
What melon? What tea?

82
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,420
It's premature melon.

83
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:45,620
After soaking in the spring water
the whole day,

84
00:03:45,820 --> 00:03:47,660
it is then stewed
with West Lake's Longjing tea

85
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:49,380
for the time of a stick of incense.

86
00:03:49,620 --> 00:03:51,420
Finally, drizzle it with sesame oil.

87
00:03:52,740 --> 00:03:53,820
So complicated.

88
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:54,860
It must be delicious.

89
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:57,100
How come you don't know about it,
but she knows.

90
00:04:04,980 --> 00:04:06,340
Isn't this bitter gourd?

91
00:04:06,540 --> 00:04:07,900
It's premature melon.

92
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:11,660
This used to be your favorite food.

93
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,660
You haven't had it for a while.
Are you not used to it anymore?

94
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:16,140
Have some more.

95
00:04:17,660 --> 00:04:18,940
I'm not hungry right now.

96
00:04:19,220 --> 00:04:21,420
It's not easy for you
to come to the palace.

97
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:22,940
Have some to gain more energy.

98
00:04:23,220 --> 00:04:25,620
I can eat all this stuff
whenever I want.

99
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:26,420
You have some.

100
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:30,140
One must respect seniority.

101
00:04:30,340 --> 00:04:31,500
You go first.

102
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:32,940
Go ahead.

103
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:33,860
Here.

104
00:04:33,860 --> 00:04:34,740
Have some.

105
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:36,060
You go first.

106
00:04:36,060 --> 00:04:38,020
You have some.

107
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:38,820
You have some first.

108
00:04:39,900 --> 00:04:41,900
If you don't eat, I'll be mad.

109
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:44,060
I especially prepared this for you.

110
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,260
Tasty.

111
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:57,780
Very delicious.

112
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:02,460
By the way,

113
00:05:03,380 --> 00:05:05,340
it's been a while
since you came to the palace.

114
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:07,620
Why is there still no news?

115
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:09,700
What news?

116
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:12,740
I noticed that Her Majesty

117
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:14,380
doesn't like you very much.

118
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:17,420
How can you become
the Crown Princess like this?

119
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:19,300
The Crown Princess?

120
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:23,740
Don't forget what your father told you

121
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:24,980
before you left for the palace.

122
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:26,780
You have two older brothers back home

123
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:28,460
who have always been good kids.

124
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,980
If you can be the Crown Princess,

125
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:33,060
you'll be able to help them one day.

126
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:34,100
Stop it.

127
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:37,340
So you ask Mei Yushan
to come to the palace

128
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:38,660
for that purpose.

129
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:41,500
That's also for your own good.

130
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:42,500
You...

131
00:05:43,260 --> 00:05:44,820
Are you really going to use Shan

132
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,220
to gain glory for the Mei Family?

133
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:50,940
She said that for me.

134
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:52,700
Shan.

135
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:55,660
I'm sad to hear you say that.

136
00:05:56,100 --> 00:05:58,460
Mulan joined the army for her father.

137
00:05:58,540 --> 00:06:00,380
Zhaojun married a foreigner
for her country.

138
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,660
I am simply asking you

139
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:05,940
to help your brothers
get a brighter future.

140
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:07,260
There's nothing wrong with that.

141
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:11,460
Mulan joined the army
because her father was old.

142
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:13,500
Zhaojun's marriage was also absurd.

143
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:14,660
A country actually

144
00:06:14,660 --> 00:06:16,940
asked a woman
to take all the responsibilities.

145
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,500
The Western Han Dynasty
gained peace through that.

146
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:20,540
But no one cared about

147
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,740
whether the bride was scared and upset.

148
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,340
You've taught Shan how to write
and play the guqin

149
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:25,060
since she was a child.

150
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:27,380
Is it only to ask Shan

151
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:28,900
to sacrifice herself
to support her brothers?

152
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:30,220
I didn't say that.

153
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:31,900
She said it for me.

154
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,180
Anyway.

155
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:37,660
Millions of women

156
00:06:37,860 --> 00:06:39,500
have done such things before.

157
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:41,420
So your daughter

158
00:06:41,620 --> 00:06:43,220
has to repeat someone else's tragedy?

159
00:06:43,540 --> 00:06:44,540
Exactly.

160
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,060
Shan, listen.

161
00:06:50,340 --> 00:06:53,860
The Crown Prince is intelligent,
upright,

162
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:55,140
and handsome.

163
00:06:55,540 --> 00:06:57,060
I really don't understand

164
00:06:57,140 --> 00:06:59,380
what's so wrong with you marrying him.

165
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:00,220
No.

166
00:07:00,580 --> 00:07:02,900
Marriage should happen
between two people in love.

167
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:07,820
I said all I had to say.

168
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:10,260
It's getting late. I need to go home.

169
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,580
Now you know why my parents
asked me to enter the palace.

170
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,220
Will you despise me?

171
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:27,660
Nonsense.

172
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:29,220
How could I despise you?

173
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:30,620
I actually envy you.

174
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:35,940
In fact,

175
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:37,940
I envy you,

176
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:39,340
because your mother

177
00:07:39,340 --> 00:07:40,500
comes to visit you when you're ill.

178
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:42,100
What's wrong?

179
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,380
When I was a child,

180
00:07:44,580 --> 00:07:46,700
I always asked my three fathers

181
00:07:47,180 --> 00:07:48,340
about my mother's identity

182
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,660
and her appearance.

183
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:52,260
They all got tired of me.

184
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:53,380
So they'd avoid me.

185
00:07:56,300 --> 00:07:59,820
I just wanted to know who I really was.

186
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:02,740
I wanted to know

187
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:05,500
if it was really like what others said

188
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,580
that because my mother didn't like me
and hated me,

189
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:10,700
she abandoned me.

190
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:12,900
These awful people.

191
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:14,940
I am here for you.

192
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:16,100
No one can ever hurt you again.

193
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:18,420
I will be there for you, too.

194
00:08:18,420 --> 00:08:19,740
No one can hurt you.

195
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:25,020
You didn't see her face clearly?

196
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,220
The room was quite dark.

197
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:27,820
She ran away
as soon as Mrs. Mei arrived.

198
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:31,220
Why do you suddenly want me
to keep an eye on that maid?

199
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:37,900
I hope this has nothing
to do with Douzi.

200
00:08:38,540 --> 00:08:39,340
Otherwise,

201
00:08:40,540 --> 00:08:41,780
there will be a huge trouble.

202
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:44,260
Ladies, please wake up.

203
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:46,300
Her Majesty summons you.

204
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:48,260
She's already at the Chongwen Academy.

205
00:08:53,780 --> 00:08:55,860
She's already at the Chongwen Academy.

206
00:08:57,740 --> 00:08:58,860
Douzi.

207
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:00,260
Where is my braised pork leg?

208
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:02,540
Douzi, wake up.

209
00:09:02,980 --> 00:09:06,060
I'll take beggar's chicken,
lotus duck, and pig's kidney

210
00:09:06,060 --> 00:09:07,020
to go.

211
00:09:07,140 --> 00:09:07,860
The dishes are ready.

212
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:10,580
Where is the pork leg?

213
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:12,940
Ladies, please wake up.

214
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:15,580
Her Majesty summons you.

215
00:09:17,020 --> 00:09:18,740
She's already at the Chongwen Academy.

216
00:09:37,780 --> 00:09:40,980
Greetings, Your Majesty.

217
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:43,780
The palace opens this academy

218
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:46,140
to teach and enlighten

219
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:48,540
everyone of you

220
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:51,500
to understand what to do

221
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,020
and what not to do.

222
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:58,420
It's only been a few days
since you've been here.

223
00:09:58,580 --> 00:10:00,500
Yet someone has already caused trouble.

224
00:10:00,660 --> 00:10:01,980
The whole palace is

225
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,340
now gossiping about it.

226
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:06,900
I thought I got away with it yesterday.

227
00:10:07,260 --> 00:10:09,020
Why does she come
to pick on me again today?

228
00:10:11,060 --> 00:10:14,180
I have to punish you today

229
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:15,700
to set an example.

230
00:10:16,180 --> 00:10:16,900
Someone coming.

231
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:19,580
Arrest Mei Yushan...

232
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,420
Mei Yushan's

233
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:27,500
maid.

234
00:10:32,020 --> 00:10:34,300
Stop! Stop! Let go of her.

235
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,460
What crime did Mei commit?

236
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,420
What crime?

237
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:40,780
A capital crime.

238
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:44,820
What happened?

239
00:10:51,540 --> 00:10:52,700
Why are you so happy?

240
00:10:55,580 --> 00:10:57,780
Her Majesty came
to the Guixiu Pavilion today.

241
00:10:58,380 --> 00:11:01,820
I guess she was here
to punish Mei Yushan

242
00:11:02,060 --> 00:11:03,860
for making the Crown Prince
fall into the water.

243
00:11:07,180 --> 00:11:08,660
My Lady, you may not know.

244
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:11,980
It wasn't Miss Mei
who was saved by His Highness.

245
00:11:12,060 --> 00:11:13,780
It was her maid, Mei.

246
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:16,860
Mei?

247
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:19,140
Are you sure?

248
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:23,500
